entries.description: It’s time to defund NPR over how it promotes porn for kids. The network ran an essay by ‘Gender Queer’ author that omits how her book included sex drawings.

entries.title: Kirk Cameron, 'responding to the cries of parents' who 'feel bullied,' is headed to more public libraries
entries.description: Actor-writer Kirk Cameron will travel to more public libraries across America, he told Fox News Digital, to share messages of faith, family and love of country with parents and children.

entries.title: Inspired by Ukraine, Taiwan seeks to bolster military preparedness as China threat continues
entries.description: Spurred by Beijing's bellicose behavior and inspired by the Ukrainian resistance to Russia’s invasion, Taiwan is returning to a one-year military conscription policy for men over 18.

entries.title: Kate Hudson, Lily-Rose Depp and more stars fire back at the 'nepo baby' label
entries.description: Stars including Kate Hudson, Lily-Rose Depp, Tom Hanks, Hailey Bieber and others have voiced their opinions as the "nepo-babies" debate rages in Hollywood.

entries.title: Washington Post slammed for 'normalizing,' 'minimizing' pedophilia: ‘Part of the depravity’
entries.description: The Washington Post dismissed concerns over a book featuring oral sex between young boys only a few weeks after fawning over a play that normalizes sexual predators.

entries.title: Investigators remove items from home of missing Massachusetts mother Ana Walshe
entries.description: Officials took equipment into the home of missing Massachusetts mother Ana Walshe on Sunday and removed items from the property. She has been missing since New Year's Day.

entries.title: Aaron Rodgers denies jersey swap after loss to Lions, retirement speculation begins
entries.description: Now that the Green Bay Packers are out of the playoffs, Aaron Rodgers' future will be the next big question to answer. He added fuel to that fire following the loss.

entries.title: On this day in history, Jan. 9, 2007, Steve Jobs introduces Apple iPhone at Macworld in San Francisco
entries.description: Steve Jobs introduced the iPhone, Apple's first smartphone, at the Macworld Expo in San Francisco on this day in history, Jan. 9, 2007. The product changed society and Apple's bottom line.

entries.title: NFL playoffs set as final week of 2022 regular season ends
entries.description: The Buffalo Bills, Cincinnati Bengals, Jacksonville Jaguars, San Francisco 49ers, Minnesota Vikings and Tampa Bay Buccaneers will be in the wild-card round.

entries.title: Lions play spoiler, knock Packers out of playoffs behind Jamaal Williams' two touchdowns
entries.description: The Detroit Lions, with nothing to play for, came into Lambeau Field and played spoiler, knocking the Green Bay Packers out of the playoffs with a Week 18 win.

entries.title: Texans part ways with Lovie Smith after one season as head coach
entries.description: The Houston Texans announced they have fired head coach Lovie Smith after just one season. Smith had three years left on his deal, but after a 3-13-1 record, they're moving on.

entries.title: Packers' Quay Walker pushes member of Lions training staff, gets ejected from game
entries.description: Green Bay Packers' linebacker Quay Walker was ejected from Sunday night's game after he pushed a member of the Detroit Lions' training staff.

entries.title: Prince Harry's Top 5 '60 Minutes' Bombshells
entries.description: Prince Harry took psychedelic drugs, bashed Prince William and called Camilla a "villain" in scathing review of royals in "60 Minutes" with Anderson Cooper.

entries.title: Prince Harry fears 'tabloid media' will radicalize its readers into causing 'harm' to his wife and children
entries.description: CBS’ “60 Minutes” aired an interview between Prince Harry and correspondent Anderson Cooper on Sunday ahead of the release of Harry's new memoir “Spare.”

entries.title: 49ers fan falls from stands as he tries to catch towel
entries.description: A San Francisco 49ers fan fell from the stands as he tried to catch a towel thrown by Brock Purdy after the team's win over the Arizona Cardinals.

entries.title: Mark Levin warns House GOP: 'If you don't unite to fight tyranny, the people will rise up against you'
entries.description: Fox News host Mark Levin breaks down Kevin McCarthy's narrow win and what Republicans need to do to earn voters' trust in his opening monologue on 'Life Liberty& Levin.'

entries.title: Cardinals' JJ Watt emotional during standing ovation in final game
entries.description: Arizona Cardinals defensive end J.J. Watt was emotional as Levi's Stadium gave him a standing ovation in his final NFL game. Watt finished his career with 114.5 sacks.

entries.title: Georgia man arrested after fleeing troopers on motorcycle and posting video to TikTok
entries.description: Clayton County Police and Georgia State Police arrested a man who fled police on a rare motorcycle, then posted the video to TikTok and YouTube.

entries.title: Taiwan's defense ministry says dozens of Chinese military aircraft entered air space near island
entries.description: Taiwan's defense ministry said on Sunday that 57 Chinese military aircraft and four ships were detected near the island amid increased tensions.

entries.title: Biden sees 'sanitized' border crisis as migrant encounters plummet at El Paso and encampments cleared: sources
entries.description: U.S. Customs and Border Protection sources said President Biden got a "sanitized" version of the border crisis in El Paso, Texas, as migrant encounters plummeted since December.

entries.title: Bengals' Joe Mixon answers ex-NFL star's call for coin-flip celebration, Chad Johnson vows to pay fine
entries.description: Cincinnati Bengals running back Joe Mixon stepped up to the plate and delivered for former NFL star Chad Johnson on Sunday against the Baltimore Ravens.

entries.title: Florida Rep. Byron Donalds reveals committee appointment in exchange for McCarthy House Speaker vote
entries.description: Rep. Byron Donalds, R-Fla., revealed Sunday he has been appointed to the Republican House Steering Committee in exchange for supporting Kevin McCarthy for House Speaker.

entries.title: Rep. Mike Rogers apologizes to Gaetz after tense confrontation on House floor: 'I briefly lost my temper'
entries.description: Rep. Mike Rogers, R-Ala., and Rep. Matt Gaetz, R-Fla., made amends on Sunday after a tense encounter on the House floor during chaotic speaker votes on Friday evening.

entries.title: Seahawks remain in playoff picture with overtime win over Rams
entries.description: The Seattle Seahawks did their part to stay alive in the NFC playoff race on Sunday, securing an overtime victory over the Los Angeles Rams.

entries.title: Russell Wilson, Broncos finish disappointing year on positive note with win over Chargers
entries.description: Russell Wilson and the Denver Broncos finished their disappointing season with a win, defeating the Los Angeles Chargers, 31-28, on Sunday.

entries.title: Sam Howell leads Commanders to win over Cowboys in first career start
entries.description: Rookie quarterback Sam Howell collected a victory in his first career start, leading the Washington Commanders over the Dallas Cowboys on Sunday.

entries.title: California's Newsom blames climate change, to seek federal assistance as more storms line up to batter state
entries.description: California Gov. Gavin Newsom held a press conference on Sunday, where he said he was requesting federal assistance through an emergency declaration.

entries.title: White Sox closer Liam Hendriks announces he has cancer
entries.description: Chicago White Sox closer Liam Hendriks announced Sunday that he has been diagnosed with non-Hodgkin's lymphoma via Instagram. His treatment begins Monday.

entries.title: Prince Harry accuses royal family of being 'complicit' in Meghan's 'pain and suffering'
entries.description: Meghan Markle suffered at the hands of the royal family, Prince Harry said while detailing how the monarchy had a "responsibility" to "learn and grow."

entries.title: Chris Rufo scorches the Washington Post for its latest CRT 'lies,' paper forced to issue correction
entries.description: Chris Rufo called out the Washington Post on Sunday for an article with several inaccuracies that led the news outlet to issue a correction.

entries.title: German police detain Iranians accused of plotting 'Islamist-motivated attack' after US tip
entries.description: German police arrested two Iranian men accused of plotting an "Islamist-motivated attack" after receiving a tip from U.S. security officials, according to law enforcement.

entries.title: Browns part ways with Bernie Kosar after former NFL star places bet on team to win
entries.description: The Cleveland Browns parted ways with Bernie Kosar after the former quarterback placed a bet on the team to beat the Pittsburgh Steelers.

entries.title: Jalen Hurts leads Eagles to first-round bye in win over Giants
entries.description: Jalen Hurts returned to MVP form in his first game back since a shoulder injury. He led the Philadelphia Eagles to a Week 18 win over the New York Giants.

entries.title: Biden departs El Paso after brief border visit without seeing most impacted areas, critics say
entries.description: President Biden left El Paso Sunday after a border visit, but critics say he did not go to the areas where illegal immigration is the biggest problem.

entries.title: Russell Wilson, Derwin James kneel in prayer before Broncos-Chargers game
entries.description: Denver Broncos quarterback Russell Wilson and Los Angeles Chargers safety Derwin James met for a prayer before their game Sunday afternoon.

entries.title: Brock Purdy tallies 3 touchdown passes, 49ers pick up 10th straight win
entries.description: Brock Purdy led the San Francisco 49ers to their 10th consecutive win to end the regular season on the highest of notes against the Arizona Cardinals.

entries.title: Bills' John Brown gives touchdown ball to trainer who administered CPR to Damar Hamlin
entries.description: Bills wide receiver John Brown did something very special with his touchdown ball on Sunday, giving it to the Bills trainer who administered CPR to save Damar Hamlin's life.

entries.title: TikTok, Meta sued by Seattle school district for allegedly wreaking mental health crisis among students
entries.description: TikTok, Meta, Snap and YouTube were sued for allegedly causing a mental health crisis among Seattle public school teenagers, according to a lawsuit.
